==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pembroke table
<hw>Pem"broke ta`ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[From
<etsep>Pembroke</etsep>, a town and shire in Wales.]</ety> <def>A style
of four-legged drop-leaf table in vogue in England, chiefly in the later
Georgian period.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The characteristic which gives a table the name of
<qex>Pembroke</qex> consists in the drop leaves, which are held up, when
the table is open, by brackets which turn under the top.</q> <rj><qau>F.
C. Morse.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pemmican</ent>⟦br⟧
